mlFuAKnDcXP1jsItL6ZBUD2bhwlbMI87S_f01hkf7b7Qu4g8W73FHxz5uXMwy2tCt4SJKP7FGC7ClWqpGNr8ickNnHubBc8pCU8ING665yakPeSCpKpI-0Km8fG2sqPQOx5HwgainLZoCqaGKtnz_sIh2csHicNH0FEF1B3zYdt_6mxg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Hibernate behavior**\\n\\nI’m thinking about mapping file paths in the hibernate-processor jar. The default mapping file includes /META-INF/orm.xml along with context ormXmlFiles. If a resource like /META-INF/services/javax.annotation.processing.Processor is present, getResource should find it, even if it’s not XML. I’m curious whether loadEntityMappings handles parsing errors and continues successfully. It seems the ormXml option could also return success with a warning for invalid XML. Is that supported behavior?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Gradle test classpath**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the Gradle test classpath, which generally includes the test classes and resources. Even if processTestResources doesn’t use the source, the path might still be included. If we create something at runtime before invoking the parser, the AppClassLoader can probably find it. In a native image, runtime-created resources won’t be included, and we might avoid annotation processing. I’m considering creating a fake Context and figuring out the parser path while handling relevant options.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining resource loading**\\n\\nI'm looking into the loading process for entity mappings, particularly how the ResourceStreamLocator's getResource can throw an exception while getResourceAsStream might return null for the default. When the service stream is non-null, mappingBinder.bind could catch an invalid warning. It seems the context's isFullyXmlConfigured is false, leading to empty loops in determineAnnotationAccessTypes. I'll need to access ProcessingEnvironment's methods like getOptions and getFiler later on, while considering how HibernateProcessor initializes handleSettings.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_9ozdnFa1VyWaxXWwij9HlWlE|fc_047c98cbc5071205016a353bc4a89481948277ddca761d9960", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1 -name '*.jar' | while read j; do if jar tf \"$j\" 2>/dev/null | grep -qx 'META-INF/orm.xml'; then echo \"$j\"; fi; done | head -20", "timeout": 60}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1 -name '*.jar' | while read j; do if jar tf \\\"$j\\\" 2>/dev/null | grep -qx 'META-INF/orm.xml'; then echo \\\"$j\\\"; fi; done | head -20\",\"timeout\":60}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 910, "output": 1822, "cacheRead": 41472, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44204, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781873564709, "responseId": "resp_047c98cbc5071205016a353b9d805c819492b09655aa29b25b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_9ozdnFa1VyWaxXWwij9HlWlE|fc_047c98cbc5071205016a353bc4a89481948277ddca761d9960", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Command timed out after 60 seconds"}], "details": {}, "isError": true, "timestamp": 1781873665351}]}
