[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `tests/src/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-processor/7.2.6.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_orm/hibernate_processor/JpaDescriptorParserTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Removed the in-process `JavaCompiler` path.
[assistant] - Now drives `JpaDescriptorParser` directly through its public constructor with a minimal `ProcessingEnvironment`.
[assistant] - Pre-populates Hibernate’s lazy XML timestamp cache with a stale serialized `FileTimeStampChecker`.
[assistant] - Calls `parseMappingXml()` twice:
[assistant]   - First call reaches:
[assistant]     - `Class#getResource(...)`
[assistant]     - `ObjectInputStream#readObject()`
[assistant]     - `ObjectOutputStream#writeObject(...)`
[assistant]   - Second call reuses the rewritten timestamp cache.
[assistant] 
[assistant] This avoids relying on classpath resource visibility while still covering the requested dynamic-access call sites in `JpaDescriptorParser`.
